. `x ⧏ y` means that `0 ⧏ y - x`.\nSee `PGame.lf_iff_sub_zero_lf`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/PGame/Order.html#SetTheory.PGame.«term_⧏_»","kind":"def","line":62,"name":"SetTheory.PGame.«term_⧏_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/SetTheory/PGame/Order.lean#L62-L63"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/PGame/Order.html#SetTheory.PGame.LF\"><span class=\"name\">SetTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">PGame</span>.<span class=\"name\">LF</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x </span><span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/PGame/Basic.html#SetTheory.PGame\">PGame</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The less or fuzzy relation on pre-games. `x ⧏ y` is defined as `¬ y ≤ x`.\n\nIf `0 ⧏ x`, then Left can win `x` as the first player. `x ⧏ y` means that `0 ⧏ y - x`.\nSee `PGame.lf_iff_sub_zero_lf`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/PGame/Order.html#SetTheory.PGame.LF","kind":"def","line":55,"name":"SetTheory.PGame.LF","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/SetTheory/PGame/Order.lean#L55-L60"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/PGame/Order.html#SetTheory.PGame.le\"><span class=\"name\">SetTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">PGame</span>.<span class=\"name\">le</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE\">LE</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/PGame/Basic.html#SetTheory.PGame\">PGame</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The less or equal relation on pre-games.\n\nIf `0 ≤ x`, then Left can win `x` as the second player. `x ≤ y` means that `0 ≤ y - x`.\nSee `PGame.le_iff_sub_nonneg`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/PGame/Order.html#SetTheory.PGame.le","kind":"instance","line":46,"name":"SetTheory.PGame.le","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/SetTheory/PGame/Order.lean#L46-L53"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Logic.Small.Defs","Mathlib.Order.GameAdd","Mathlib.SetTheory.PGame.Basic","Mathlib.Tactic.Linter.DeprecatedModule"],"instances":[{"className":"LE","name":"SetTheory.PGame.le","typeNames":["SetTheory.PGame"]},{"className":"Preorder","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instPreorder","typeNames":["SetTheory.PGame"]},{"className":"Std.Irrefl","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instIrreflLF","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Trans","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instTransLeLF","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Trans","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instTransLFLe","typeNames":[]},{"className":"IsEquiv","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instIsEquivEquiv","typeNames":["SetTheory.PGame","SetTheory.PGame.Equiv"]},{"className":"Setoid","name":"SetTheory.PGame.setoid","typeNames":["SetTheory.PGame"]},{"className":"Trans","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instTransLeEquiv","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Trans","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instTransEquivLe","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Trans","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instTransLFEquiv","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Trans","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instTransEquivLF","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Trans","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instTransLtEquiv","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Trans","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instTransEquivLt","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Std.Symm","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instSymmFuzzy","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Std.Irrefl","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instIrreflFuzzy","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Coe","name":"SetTheory.PGame.instCoeRelabellingEquiv","typeNames":["SetTheory.PGame.Relabelling","HasEquiv.Equiv"]}],"name"